description:
Proper Japanese Title: 基本のキホン (Kihon no Kihon)

Abe wasn't a fan of Haruna, but there's a lot to like about the guy. He's tall, good-looking, has a one-in-a-million arm, and he wants to win no matter what.
name: The Basics of Basics

description: Proper Japanese Title: 次は？ (Tsugi Wa?)
name: What's Next?

description: Proper Japanese Title: 崎玉 (Sakitama)
name: Sakitama

description: Proper Japanese Title: 3回戦 (3 Kaisen)
name: Third Match

description: Proper Japanese Title: 野球シンドイ (Yakyuu Shindoi)
name: Baseball Is Hard

description: Proper Japanese Title: 野球やりたい (Yakyuu Yaritai)
name: I Want to Play Baseball

description: Proper Japanese Title: 大事 (Daiji)
name: Important

description: Proper Japanese Title: ゆるやかな変化 (Yuruyaka na Henka)
name: Slow Change

description: Proper Japanese Title: 5 回戦 (5 Kaisen)
name: Fifth Match

description: Proper Japanese Title: 研究されてる (Kenkyuu Sareteru)
name: Doing Research

description: Proper Japanese Title: 5回裏, 2対5 (5 kai ura, 2 tai 5)
name: Bottom Of The 5th, 2-5

description: Proper Japanese Title: エースだから (Eusu Dakara)
name: Because I'm The Ace

description: Proper Japanese Title: 9 回 (9 Kaisen)
name: 9th Inning

description: Proper Japanese Title: 目標 (Mokuhyō)
name: Goal

description: Proper Japanese Title: また始まる (Mata Hajimaru)
name: We Start Again

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 起動 (Kidō)

Takumi is an anime-obsessed recluse with a fetish for two dimensional girls. His dirty little cyber secrets land him in real-life trouble after a chatroom encounter with the mysterious General.
name: Boot Up

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 自我 (Jiga)

Takumi fears he may be losing his mind after finding the pink-haired girl from the murder scene sitting next to him in class. To make matters even worse, someone keeps snooping around his house.
name: Ego

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 接触 (Sesshoku)

A chilling flashback to a tragedy from his younger days sheds light on Takumi’s reclusive existence. Back in the present, he attends a concert given by a clairvoyant performer.
name: Contact

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 初動 (Shodō)

Haunted by visions of young girls carrying swords, Takumi begins to search for a weapon of his own. His frantic quest is complicated by an unwanted visit from the police.
name: Commencing

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 先導 (Sendō)

As the police continue to investigate him, Takumi learns the secrets of the Di-Sword from Ayase, and a cyber friend sends him a video that sheds light on the New Gen case.
name: Guidance

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 抱擁 (Hōyō)

Takumi grows dependent on Rimi’s calming presences as he struggles to discover the power of his own Di-Sword, and a cryptic phone call shakes the city to its core.
name: Embracement

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 自覚 (Jikaku)

Takumi is rescued from a group of hired thugs by a classmate with telepathic abilities. After regaining consciousness, he learns the identity of the evil mastermind behind the earthquake.
name: Realization

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 連動 (Rendō)

The Gigalomaniac Trio embarks on a daring mission to destroy Noah II, but their enemy remains a step ahead, ambushing the would-be heroes with their own worst nightmares.
name: Linkage

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 拒絶 (Kyozetsu)

Yua goes to the police with information concerning Takumi, who receives a disturbing call for help from his little sister. Meanwhile, another New Gen incident occurs!
name: Rejection

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 洗礼 (Senrei)

Takumi realizes the horrific truth about his troubled existence, Yua confronts the delusion of her dead sister, and Rimi attempts to rescue Nanami.
name: Purification

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 自立 (Jiritsu)

The General and Takumi meet face-to-face to discuss their shared existence. Later, after awakening his Di-Sword, Takumi goes underground for a showdown with an artificial gigalomaniac!
name: Independence

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 使命 (Shimei)

Takumi finally realizes his ultimate destiny: to destroy Noah II. But first, he must conquer the illusion of fear and defeat the one man standing in his way.
name: Mission

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王、笹塚に立つ (Maō, Sasazuka ni Tatsu)

When the lord of demons and his horde waged war against the humans in their realm, a hero vanquished their army. Cornered, the Devil fled through an interdimensional portal to Earth. He vows to one day reign again, but until then... he needs a job!
name: The Devil Arrives In Sasazuka

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 勇者、仕事優先で魔王城に泊まる (Yūsha, Shigoto Yūsen de Maōjō ni Tomaru)

When Emilia the hero finally tracks down the ruler of demons here on Earth, he's not exactly what she was expecting. Which may or may not make her a little crazy.
name: The Hero Stays At the Devil's Castle For Work Reasons

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王、新宿で後輩とデートする (Maō, Shinjuku de Kōhai to Dēto Suru)

Something supernatural seems to be going on with Chiho. Meanwhile, it's possible Maou doesn't really understand the concept of a "date"... but it's not long before everyone has much bigger problems on their hands.
name: The Devil Goes On A Date With His Junior In Shinjuku

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 勇者、心の温かさに触れる (Yūsha, Kokoro no Atatakasa ni Fureru)

In the aftermath of the cave-in, Emi sees a side of Maou that doesn't jibe with the demonic king she knew in Ente Isla. Meanwhile, everyone sees a side of the landlady that nobody could have expected...
name: The Hero Experiences Human Warmth

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王と勇者、笹塚を救う (Maō to Yūsha, Sasazuka o Sukuu)

Lucifer is wrecking the neighborhood in a big way, and he's brought along some unexpected friends! To save both themselves and their new Earthly home, can Emi, Maou, and Ashiya do the impossible and... work together?!
name: The Devil and the Hero Save Sasazuka

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王、学校の階段を昇る (Maō, Gakkō no Kaidan o Noboru)

Back in Ente Isla, the other high priests find out about Olba's betrayal. Meanwhile, Lucifer's moved into the Devil's Castle and gotten Maou and Ashiya into school ghost stories.
name: The Devil Climbs the Stairway To School

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王、近所付き合いで家計を助けられる (Maō, Kinjozukiai de Kakei o Tasukerareru)

Maou and company find that a young lady named Suzuno has moved in next door. She is quick to make friends and starts helping them out, which causes Emi to wonder what her motives are.
name: The Devil's Budget Is Saved By Neighborliness

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 勇者、修羅場に突入する (Yūsha, Shuraba ni Totsunyū Suru)

Emi and Suzuno have some truly epic miscommunications, but when they finally get those straightened out, they're even less on the same page than before. Meanwhile, Maou's got bigger (?) problems: there's a new fast-food restaurant in town!
name: The Hero Enters the Fray

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 勇者、修羅場を経験する (Yūsha, Shuraba o Keiken Suru)

Insisting that Emi and Suzuno need an impartial third party to resolve their dispute, Rika goes with them to meet Maou. Meanwhile, Maou tries to handle the loss of business caused by the opening of a new restaurant.
name: The Hero Experiences A Fray

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王と勇者、いつもと違った日常を過ごす (Maō to Yūsha, Itsumo to Chigatta Nichijō o Sugosu)

It's a busy day at the local amusement park, with crowded restaurants, animals on the loose, scary ghosts, and a much-needed swimwear intervention.
name: The Devil and the Hero Take A Break From the Daily Routine

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 勇者、己の信念を貫く (Yūsha, Onore no Shinnen o Tsuranuku)

The stranger Suzuno met at the train station has her reconsidering her position on the Devil. Emi, however, is unwavering.
name: The Hero Stays True To Her Convictions

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王、己の職責を果たす (Maō, Onore no Shokuseki o Hatasu)

The archangel Sariel is willing to torture people to get what he wants, and he's confident that no one can stop him--but he didn't realize quite how seriously Maou takes his responsibilities.
name: The Devil Carries Out His Duties

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 魔王と勇者、真っ当に仕事に励む (Maō to Yūsha, Mattō ni Shigoto ni Hagemu)

Ashiya has something he needs to talk to his master about in private. Are the demons going back to Ente Isla?!
name: The Devil and the Hero Do Some Honest Hard Work

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ばらかこどん /元気な子供 (Barakakodon /Genkina Kodomo)

A calligrapher is sent to an island after causing a commotion. There he meets a young girl who would inspire him to a world he has never seen before.
name: Barakakodon (Spirited Child)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: やかましか /うるさい (Yakamashika /Urusai)

Handa, seeking to work on his calligraphy, is being "bothered" by the carefree residents of the island. This time, to the point he's hospitalized.
name: Yakamashika (Noisy)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ひとんもち /お祝いで投げられる餅 (Hitonmochi /Oiwai de nagerareru Mochi)

Handa's sends in his calligraphy work, only to find he was awarded a "disappointing" second place... Handa's daily life continues.
name: Hitonmochi (Rice Cakes Thrown in Celebrations)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: しまんおんつぁんどん /島の親父たち (Shiman ontsandon /Shima no Oyajitachi)

Handa is caught by Miwa's father to work on writing the name of his ship, where he gains a new perspective on approach towards calligraphy.
name: Shiman Ontsuandon (Men of the Island)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: うんにおえぎいっ　/海に泳ぎに行く (Un ni oegii /Umi ni oyogi ni iku)

With the next exhibition closing in, Handa is asked to take the kids swimming, where he finds out that there's more to life than just calligraphy.
name: Unnioegi (Going to the Sea to Swim)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: よそんもん　/東京から来た奴ら (Yosonmon /Toukyou kara kita Yatsura)

Guests have arrived, and one of them, Kanzaki, cast Handa into confusion. Handa responds back as one who has lived with the people on the island.
name: Yosonmon (The Guys from Tokyo)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ひさんいを /高級な魚 (Hisan-Iwo /Koukyuuna Sakana)

Handa’s guests spend their last day on the island going fishing. Handa learns that he can inspire others just as he has been inspired.
name: Hisanio (An Expensive Fish)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: オンデ /念仏踊り (Onde /Nenbutsu Odori)

Handa experiences summer on the island, and sees a different side of Naru when he joins her in paying a visit to her family grave.
name: Onde (Buddhist Chanting and Dancing)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: おけがまくっちした　/大怪我しそうになった (Okega Makucchishita /Ookega shisouni natta)

With the Narukain exhibit closing in, Handa is starting to feel the pressure again. He gains the inspiration to write his work, but...
name: Okega Makucchishita (Was Almost Seriously Injured)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: だっちいこで　/みんなで行こう (Dacchi Ikode/ Minna de ikou)

After completing his submission, Handa turns his attention to the island and its residents; Naru gets a surprise when she goes to pay Handa a visit.
name: Dacchi Ikode (Let's Go Together)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 東京にいます　/よせおっ (Toukyou ni imasu/ Yoseo)

Handa is back in Tokyo for an important meeting. When he really starts feeling the pressure, he finds comfort in an unexpected phone call.
name: I'm In Tokyo (Yoseo)

description:
Proper Japanese Title: かえってきてうりしか (Kaette Kite Urishika)

With a few more loose ends to tend to, Handa is ready to go back to the island. Smiling faces and open arms await Handa's return.
name: Happy Yer Home
Tigh Me Up, Tigh Me Down

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Direct Confrontation with Piccolo!! An Angry Masenko in the Heavenly Realm

Japanese: Pikkoro to Kyokusetsu Taiketsu!! Tenkai ni Ikari no Masenkō (ピッコロと直接対決!!天界に怒りの魔せん光)

With Piccolo infected by the Black Water Mist and Kami trapped in a glass bottle, Garlic Jr. allows his Spice Boys to “have sport” with Earth’s heroic defenders. Will Spice’s energy blast finish off Krillin for good?
name: Fight With Piccolo

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Retrieve Everyone's Minds!! The Ultra Holy Water Resting in the Temple

Japanese: Minna no Kokoro o Torimodose!! Shinden ni Nemuru Chō Shinsui (みんなの心を取り戻せ!!神殿に眠る超神水)

Krillin, after suffering a Spice Boys beating, attempts to free Kami and Mr. Popo, but he soon falls prey to the Black Water Mist. Gohan is the only hero left who can save the Earth, but can he do it with his two best friends against him?
name: Call For Restoration

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Can't Wait Until Morning!! Kami-sama Determines a Suicidal Course of Action

Japanese: Asa made Matenai!! Kamisama no Kakugo o Kimeta Kesshikō (朝まで待てない!!神様の覚悟をきめた決死行)

Piccolo and Krillin spring their trap, revealing that they have pretended to be infected by the Black Water Mist! Enraged, Garlic Jr. transforms using the energy of the Makyo Star and warns that the Sacred Water’s effectiveness will soon expire.

Asa made Matenai!! Kamisama no Kakugo o Kimeta Kesshikō" (朝まで待てない!!神様の覚悟をきめた決死行)
name: Suicidal Course

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A Battle of Extreme Measures!! Kami-sama Breaks the Covenant

Japanese: Chō Kageki ni Shōbu da!! Okite Yaburi no Kamisama (超過激に勝負だ!!掟やぶりの神様)

Garlic Junior and his Spice Boys harness the evil power of the Makyo Star to become stronger than ever, but Gohan, Krillin, and Piccolo are ready to battle this new threat!
name: Extreme Measures

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Ultra Holy Water Worked!! The World Awakens from Its Nightmare

Japanese: Kiita ze Chō Shinsui!! Sekai ga Akumu kara Sameta (効いたぜ超神水!!世界が悪夢からさめた)

In a last ditch effort to save his friends, Gohan launches an all out assault on Garlic Junior! Meanwhile, deep within the Lookout, Kami and Mr. Popo are under siege by the Former Guardians!
name: The World Awakens

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Gohan's Brief Chance for Victory!! Blast the Makyo World...

Japanese: Gohan ni Isshun no Shōki!! Ano Makyōsei o Ute... (悟飯に一瞬の勝機!!あの魔凶星を撃て…)

Blinded by rage and desperate to destroy his enemies, Garlic Junior uses his power to open up the Dead Zone! With Piccolo and Krillin out of commission, Gohan is the only one left who can stop him!
name: Brief Chance for Victory

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: You're My Guy... Kuririn — A 101st Proposal

Japanese: Otoko da nē...Kuririn Hyakuikkaime no Puropōzu (男だねェ…クリリン101回目のプロポーズ)

Even though peace has been restored on Earth, Krillin faces his toughest challenge ever: surviving a shopping trip with Maron! And it looks like she’s picking out a wedding dress! Are Krillin and Maron planning to tie the knot?
name: Krillin's Proposal

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: That There is Earth, Papa... The Counter-Attack of Freeza, Father and Son

Japanese: Are ga Chikyū dayo Papa... Furīza Oyako no Gyakushū (あれが地球だよパパ…フリーザ親子の逆襲)

Gohan’s cracking the books, and his new tutor is cracking the whip! But study time is almost over, for a powerful evil is racing toward the Earth! Gohan’s worst fears have come to life: Frieza has survived!
name: Frieza's Counterattack
